## 🔌 jPOS Configuration

### 1. Channel (Connection to SVFE)

```xml
<channel name="svfe-channel"
         class="org.jpos.iso.channel.ASCIIChannel"
         packager="cfg/iso87.xml"
         host="SVFE_IP"
         port="SVFE_PORT"
         connect-timeout="30000"/>
```

---

### 2. MUX Configuration

```xml
<mux name="svfe-mux" class="org.jpos.q2.iso.QMUX">
    <in>svfe-channel</in>
    <out>svfe-channel</out>
    <timeout>30000</timeout>
</mux>
```

---

## 💻 Java Integration

### Basic Forwarding

```java
ISOMsg response = mux.request(request, 30000);

if (response == null) {
    throw new ISOException("SVFE timeout");
}

return response;
```

---

## 🧠 Routing Logic (Recommended)

```java
if (isOnUs(request)) {
    return processLocally(request);
} else {
    return mux.request(request, 30000);
}
```

---

## ⚠️ Critical Rules

### 1. Preserve Message Integrity

* Do NOT modify fields incorrectly
* Maintain STAN (field 11)
* Maintain RRN (field 37)

---

### 2. Handle Timeouts

```java
if (response == null) {
    triggerReversal();
}
```

---

### 3. Logging (Mandatory)

Log:

* outbound request to SVFE
* inbound response
* latency
* RC (response code)

---

### 4. MAC / Security

* Ensure MAC is valid before forwarding
* Do not break MAC unless recalculated

